        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 5:25PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Galesburg, or 7 miles west of Battle Creek, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Battle Creek...        Galesburg...           Climax...
Gull Lake...           Augusta...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
